content.description: Stand Right under the horn, match on the slope and start pulling on obvious jugs and follow the arete. Best holds are to the left of the horn. mantle the horn, find your balance and top out using the dihedral. Don't fall!
content.location: while facing the walls from the trail, its the farthest highball to the left. Obvious arete that vaguely looks like a horn.

content.description: Approach the wall on the far left of the caves and grab a sloper with both hands. immediately above your head is a series of pockets leading right towards a sloped rail. match with hands on top to finish this problem. Elusive feet make this a fun campus! finish to the right for a little harder finish.
content.location: Left side of the caves, past the graffiti, obvious chalky pockets show you the path to victory!

content.description: Sit start on obvious jugs in the back of the cave near the crack and climb straight up the oyster like ceiling, avoid using anything on the right side of the large crack. Use underclings, shallow pockets, good crimps, precision footwork, and some slopers in order to finish inside the oyster's shell! (by all means you can top the entire boulder after that, but its 12 more feet of chossy mossy sketchiness!)
content.location: Located in the caves on the far left of the North-East Face. while facing the caves it is located in the middle between two large cracks. The rock from a little ways away looks similar to an oysters shell.
